HEADWORD: Gossat
<hw>Gos"sat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
small British marine fish (<spn>Motella tricirrata</spn>); -- called
also <altname>whistler</altname> and <altname>three-bearded
rockling</altname>.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

